    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Free Evangelical Congregational Church was gathered in Providence, Rhode Island, in
        1843. At the time, the church may have also been known as the Fourth Street Church. In 1945,
        the name of the church was changed to Hope Street Church. In 1950, the church merged with
        the Second Presbyterian Church of Providence. The Hope Street Church building became new
        home of the merged church. The church still exists today as the Providence Presbyterian
        Church.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains vital membership records and administrative records for the Hope
        Street Church in Providence, Rhode Island. The collection includes baptismal records,
        marriage records, records of deaths, membership records, church meeting minutes, governance
        records, correspondence, and the 1950 merger agreement between the Hope Street Church and
        the Second Presbyterian Church.</p>
    </scopecontent>
